extends ../layouts/main

block content
  .law-container
    .container
      h1 Constitutional Law
      .law-section
        h2 Step 1: What is Constitutional Law about?
        p Constitutional law is a body of law which defines the role, powers, and structure of different entities within a state, such as the branches of government. Most commonly, constitutional law refers to the rights and powers of individuals and the government as established by a country's constitution.
      
      .law-section
        h2 Step 2: Why do we need Constitutional Law and Solutions?
        p Constitutional law is essential for:
        ul
          ul
            li Protecting fundamental rights of citizens
            li Establishing the framework of government
            li Ensuring separation of powers
            li Providing mechanisms for legal remedies
        p Solutions include constitutional amendments, judicial review, and public legal awareness programs.
      
      .law-section
        h2 Step 3: Help and Description
        p Constitutional law governs the relationship between the state and its citizens. It encompasses fundamental rights, directive principles, and the structure of government. Key areas include:
        ul
          li Fundamental Rights (Articles 12-35)
          li Directive Principles of State Policy (Articles 36-51)
          li Fundamental Duties (Articles 51A)
          li Structure of Government (Executive, Legislature, Judiciary)
          li Emergency Provisions (Articles 352-360)
      
      .chatbot-section
        h2 Constitutional Law Chatbot
        .chatbot-container
          .chat-messages#chat-messages
            .message.bot-message
              p Welcome! I can help you with constitutional law queries. What would you like to know?
          .chat-input-container
            input(type='text', id='chat-input', placeholder='Ask about constitutional law...')
            button#send-btn Send